{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82520a47-84e2-4a9f-b8a5-71052d02021d","content":"Here's the equivalent command using Microsoft.Testing.Platform options:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key mappings:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|--------|---------------------------|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nThe `--filter` stays on the `dotnet test` side (before `--`). Everything after `--` is passed directly to the new test platform runner.\n\nYou'll also need the corresponding NuGet packages in your test project:\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0a1d61f1-3ab2-48fe-bf86-297a2da2c6e9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with coverage settings\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n- With the new platform, you can still use `dotnet test` but pass the platform-specific options after `--`, or run the test executable directly.\n- The filter argument stays before `--`, while options like `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, and format specifications go after `--`.\n- I'm mapping the old logger and collection arguments to their new platform equivalents.","outputTokens":941,"requestId":"BC4B:19764A:1B70BBB:1E86FA5:69FA9099"},"id":"0bf9c8d2-0ad4-4c27-a79f-ee5cc6b99c97","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:51:51.737Z","parentId":"f1da51a5-11fd-4651-b492-d29199932520"}
